map[type:Brand value:GitHub_with_search], map[type:Instance value:GitHub_with_search_instance_1], map[type:author_association value:NONE], map[type:comments_url value:https://api.github.com/repos/demisto/etc/issues/16151/comments], map[type:events_url value:https://api.github.com/repos/demisto/etc/issues/16151/events], map[type:html_url value:https://github.com/demisto/etc/issues/16151], map[type:state value:closed], map[type:milestone value:null], map[type:comments value:23], map[type:closed_at value:2019-06-23T12:10:59Z], map[type:body value:**Customer**
The Home Depot

**Describe the integration you'd like**
1. Querying an IP.
2. Submit a domain to Bluecat Address Manager and it will be added to a response policy

**Product**
Bluecat Address Manager
https://www.bluecatnetworks.com/platform/management/
[BAM API guide 8.3.0](https://usermanual.wiki/Pdf/bamapiguide830.130556227/view)

**Usecases**
1. Querying an IP (for enrichment - Subnets applied to, hostname, etc.)
2. Modifying response policies 
Add entries to response policies - Add a domain to response policy.
As written by the customer - 
```BlueCat has response policies. These are essentially forced responses for DNS queries. We use them to do things like domain sink holing.  We have a couple of response policies with different names.```

**ETA**
Mid April

map[type:Brand value:GitHub_with_search], map[type:Instance value:GitHub_with_search_instance_1], map[type:html_url value:https://github.com/demisto/etc/pull/17645], map[type:node_id value:MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MjkxMTI4ODIx], map[type:locked value:false], map[type:comments value:0], map[type:closed_at value:2019-06-24T13:20:48Z], map[type:body value:## Status
- [x] Ready

## Description
Solves issue to all of those who experience issues with node consuming all of their CPU when running `npm start`, the fix is to run `npm install fsevents`.
The issue was the node was constantly monitoring all of the files in the web-client instead of listening for file changes, this library gives node access to the native ios file system events watchers and then node is notified when a file is changed.
